%section.hero.is-success
  .hero-body
    .container
      %h1.title Rules
      %h2.subtitle All of Chutney's linting rules
        
      %p.block
        Chutney has a long list of rules to help you build best-practice in your Cucumber / Gherkin features.
        Using Chutney locally, you build a configuration to turn off rules (and configure others).
        
      %p.block
        There is lots more information in the Chutney documentation which you can read about
        = succeed '.' do
          %a(href='https://billyruffian.github.io/chutney/')here
          
%section.container.py-6
  %table.table.is-striped.is-fullwidth
    %thead.has-text-left
      %tr
        %th Rule
        %th Description
        %th Enabled online
    %tbody
    %tr
      %td= link_to 'Avoid full stop', page_path('rules/avoid_full_stop')
      %td Don't use a full stop in your step
      %td 
        %i.fas.fa-check.is-success
    %tr
      %td= link_to 'Avoid outline for single example', page_path('rules/avoid_outline_for_single_example')
      %td If you only have one example, don't use a Scenario Outline
      %td 
        %i.fas.fa-check.is-success
    %tr
      %td= link_to 'Avoid scripting', page_path('rules/avoid_scripting')
      %td Long scenarios aren't descriptive
      %td 
        %i.fas.fa-check.is-success
    %tr
      %td= link_to 'Avoid Typographer\'s Quotes', page_path('rules/avoid_typographers_quotes')
      %td You have curly-quotes in your scenario
      %td 
        %i.fas.fa-check.is-success
    %tr
      %td= link_to 'Background Does More Than Setup', page_path('rules/background_does_more_than_setup')
      %td You are trying to do too much in your background step
      %td 
        %i.fas.fa-check.is-success
    %tr
      %td= link_to 'Background Requires Multiple Scenarios', page_path('rules/background_requires_multiple_scenarios')
      %td If you only have one scenario, don't use a background step
      %td 
        %i.fas.fa-check.is-success